- Use Java 17+ features when appropriate
- Follow Spring Boot best practices
- Use constructor injection instead of field injection
- Always include proper exception handling with custom exceptions
- Use Lombok annotations (@Data, @Builder, @Slf4j) to reduce boilerplate
- Follow REST API naming conventions (plural nouns, kebab-case)
- Always validate input using @Valid and custom validators
- Use DTOs for request/response objects, never expose entities directly
- Write service layer with @Transactional where needed
- Use meaningful variable names in Portuguese or English consistently
- Include JavaDoc for public methods in services and controllers
- Follow package structure: controller > service > repository > model > dto